Package space.sunqian.common.base.value

package space.sunqian.common.base.value
Provides interfaces and classes for value and variable.

Immutable interfaces:

  • Val;
  • BooleanVal;
  • ByteVal;
  • ShortVal;
  • CharVal;
  • IntVal;
  • LongVal;
  • FloatVal;
  • DoubleVal;
  • Ret;
Mutable interfaces:
  • Var;
  • BooleanVar;
  • ByteVar;
  • ShortVar;
  • CharVar;
  • IntVar;
  • LongVar;
  • FloatVar;
  • DoubleVar;
Range classes
  • Span
  • LongSpan
  • Class
    Description
    BooleanVal
    Primitive boolean version of Val.
    BooleanVar
    Primitive boolean version of Var.
    ByteVal
    Primitive byte version of Val.
    ByteVar
    Primitive byte version of Var.
    CharVal
    Primitive char version of Val.
    CharVar
    Primitive char version of Var.
    DoubleVal
    Primitive double version of Val.
    DoubleVar
    Primitive double version of Var.
    FloatVal
    Primitive float version of Val.
    FloatVar
    Primitive float version of Var.
    IntVal
    Primitive int version of Val.
    IntVar
    Primitive int version of Var.
    LongSpan
    LongSpan is long version of Span, consists of a startIndex inclusive and a endIndex exclusive, represents a range with long type.
    LongVal
    Primitive long version of Val.
    LongVar
    Primitive long version of Var.
    PrimitiveToVal<T>
    This interface is used to convert Val of primitive type to Val of wrapper type, such as IntVal to Val<Integer>.
    PrimitiveToVar<T,VT extends PrimitiveToVar<T,VT>>
    This interface is used to convert Var of primitive type to Var of wrapper type, such as IntVar to Var<Integer>.
    Ret<T>
    This interface represents a wrapper to wrap a return value from a method or function or other similar ones.
    ShortVal
    Primitive short version of Val.
    ShortVar
    Primitive short version of Var.
    Span
    Span consists of a startIndex inclusive and a endIndex exclusive, represents a range of a string, list or other range-able object.
    Val<T>
    This interface represents an immutable container holding a value, similar to a final variable.
    Var<T>
    This interface represents a mutable container holding a value, typically used for sharing values across scope boundaries (e.g., lambda expressions).
